In comparison with CO2RR, the photo-catalytic N2-fixation is still more demanding as dissociation enthalpy of N2 molecule triple bond (962 kJ mol−1). Normally, catalyst conversion for N2 is enormously harsh as N2 just weakly binds with solid-state catalysts and reaction entails high-energy intermediates. So, it is very much required to do an appropriate structure to support conversion competency of N2 to NH3. E0 to make the N2− is as high as − 4.2 V versus NHE via N2+e-→N2-\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
